@page "/"

<PageTitle>SharePoint File Deduplicator</PageTitle>

<h1>SharePoint File Deduplicator</h1>

<p class="lead">Welcome to the SharePoint File Deduplication Tool</p>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">What does this tool do?</h5>
                <p class="card-text">
                    This tool helps you identify and remove duplicate files in your SharePoint sites by:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Scanning SharePoint sites using Microsoft Graph API</li>
                    <li>Identifying duplicate files by calculating file hashes</li>
                    <li>Generating detailed savings reports</li>
                    <li>Replacing duplicate files with shortcuts to save space</li>
                    <li>Verifying folder navigation integrity after changes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Get Started</h5>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Ready to scan your SharePoint site for duplicates?
                </p>
                <a href="/scanner" class="btn btn-primary">Start Scanning</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5 class="card-title">How it works</h5>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Scan:</strong> Enter your SharePoint site URL and start the scan</li>
            <li><strong>Review:</strong> Review the duplicate files report and potential space savings</li>
            <li><strong>Select:</strong> Choose which file should be the "true" copy for each duplicate group</li>
            <li><strong>Replace:</strong> Replace duplicates with shortcuts pointing to the true copy</li>
            <li><strong>Verify:</strong> Verify that all shortcuts work and folder navigation is intact</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info mt-4" role="alert">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Make sure you have configured the Azure AD application with proper permissions to access SharePoint sites via Microsoft Graph API.
</div>

